<p>I want to read the following table</p>  <pre><code>#logical.table       col_a col_b row_a TRUE  FALSE row_b FALSE TRUE </code></pre>  <p>the resulting object in R should have the column and row names from the file(at least one of them) and logical columns and rows</p>  <p>I tried:</p>  <ul> <li><p><code>matrix(ncol=2, byrow=T, scan(file = 'logical.table', what=TRUE, skip=1))</code> but I miss the col/row-names.  </p></li> <li><p>deleting rownames,  <code>w&lt;-read.table(file='logical.table',   colClasses = "logical", header=T)</code> but <code>is.logical(w[1])</code> and <code>is.logical(w[1,])</code> return False  </p></li> </ul>  <p><br> <strong>Solution</strong><br> As Derwin McGeary wrote: <code>x &lt;- read.table(file="logical.table")</code> works just fine. For logical columns I use <code>x[,col]</code> and for logical rows I ended up with <code>t(x)[,row]</code>.</p>